: "Jackie Williams interviewed by Monk Rowe, New York City, New York, October 18, 1995", "collection": "hamilton", "url": "https://litsdigital.hamilton.edu/collections/object/jackie-williams-interviewed-monk-rowe-new-york-city-new-york-october-18-1995"}, {"speaker": "Frank Foster", "relation": "in music group with", "confidence": 1.0, "evidence": "a gentleman who was later to be together with me in the Count Basie Orchestra, Budd Johnson", "doc_title": "Frank Foster interviewed by Monk Rowe, Clinton, New York, April 7, 1998", "collection": "hamilton", "url": "https://litsdigital.hamilton.edu/collections/object/frank-foster-interviewed-monk-rowe-clinton-new-york-april-7-1998"}, {"speaker": "Joe Wilder", "relation": "has met", "confidence": 1.0, "evidence": "In fact, Earl Hines’s band, I had met Billy Eckstine, Budd Johnson, Pee Wee Jackson...", "doc_title": "Joe Wilder — Smithsonian Jazz Oral History", "collection": "si", "url": "https://amhistory.si.edu/jazz/Wilder-Joe/Joe-Wilder_transcription.pdf"}, {"speaker": "Patricia Willard", "relation": "in music group with", "confidence": 0.95, "evidence": "in the reed section he had Dexter Gordon, Budd Johnson, Little Johnny Jackson ... Tommy Potter playing bass. Well, Tommy got a case of pneumonia, so they called me out to substitute for him", "doc_title": "56800_John Simmons oral history interview", "collection": "rutgers", "url": "https://rucore.libraries.rutgers.edu/rutgers-lib/56800/"}, {"speaker": "David N. Baker", "relation": "in music group with", "confidence": 0.95, "evidence": "The saxophone section was Phil Woods, Gene Quill, Budd Johnson, Sahib Shihab... I joined Quincy’s band... The saxophone section was Phil Woods, Gene Quill, Budd Johnson", "doc_title": "David N. Baker — Smithsonian Jazz Oral History", "collection": "si", "url": "https://americanhistory.si.edu/sites/default/files/file-uploader/David%20N.%20Baker%20SI-NEA%20oral%20history%20%282%29.pdf"}, {"speaker": "Patricia Willard", "relation": "collaborated with", "confidence": 0.95, "evidence": "Budd Johnson worked with us occasionally too with Roy's band... We toured together again in Europe in later years. He was with Quincy's band, Quincy Jones' band.", "doc_title": "67250_John Collins oral history interview", "collection": "rutgers", "url": "https://rucore.libraries.rutgers.edu/rutgers-lib/67250/"}]}